           SHORT="schedtool can be used to query or alter a process' scheduling policy under Linux"
cat << EOF
schedtool interfaces with the Linux CPU scheduler. It allows the user to set
and query the CPU-affinity and nice-levels of processes, as well as all
scheduling policies, like batch or real-time (RR/FIFO) classes and their
priorities.

EOF
